HEADWORD: Enode
<hw>E*node"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>enodare</ets>; <ets>e</ets> out + <ets>nodare</ets> to fill with
knots, <ets>nodus</ets> a knot.]</ety> <def>To clear of knots; to make
clear.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Cockeram.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

